            . I am a Police-constable. I saw the prisoner in Old-street, about thirty or forty yards from the prosecutor's carrying this rug in this bag; I received information from a carman, and took him into custody - he said he had got a rug, which he brought from his house at Pentonville, and was going to his uncle's in Blackfriars-road.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Are you sure he said he got it from home? A. Yes.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going down old-street, and turned down Whitecross-street - two men walked before me, and dropped this - I took it up.</p>
